content:
Improved Clean Up Process for Invoice Runs

The invoice run clean-up process updates the status of invoice lines to Canceled. If the clean-up process encounters errors, decrease the clean-up's batch size to help its completion. The improved error logs help you differentiate between invoice run and clean-up errors.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions of Salesforce Billing.

How: From Setup, enter Installed Packages, select Installed Packages, click Configure for the Salesforce Billing package, go to the Invoice tab, and turn on Invoice Run Clean Up.

From Object Manager or the Picklist Value Sets setup page, add the Completed with errors value to the CleanUp Status field of the Invoice Run object. Configure the Invoice Run Clean Up Batch Size setting to define the invoice run clean-up batch size.
